---
title: Notification Module - Sequence Diagram
description: Detailed sequence of operations for notification and reminder scenarios
date: 07-03-26
---

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant FE as Frontend
    participant API as API Gateway
    participant Ctrl as Controller
    participant Svc as Service
    participant DB as MongoDB
    participant Cache as Redis
    participant Queue as BullMQ
    participant Ext as External Service
    
    %% Scenario 1: Send Task Assignment Notification
    
    note right of U: Send Task Assignment Notification
    U->>FE: Assign task to member
    FE->>API: POST /tasks {assignedUserIds}
    API->>Ctrl: create()
    Ctrl->>Svc: createTask()
    Svc->>DB: insertOne(task)
    DB-->>Svc: task created
    Svc->>Svc: enqueueNotification()
    Svc->>Queue: add('send-notification')
    Queue-->>Queue: Process job
    Queue->>Svc: processNotification()
    Svc->>DB: insertOne(notification)
    DB-->>Svc: notification created
    Svc->>Queue: add('send-push', 'send-email')
    Queue->>Ext: sendPush(FCM)
    Queue->>Ext: sendEmail(SendGrid)
    Ext-->>Queue: delivered
    Svc-->>Ctrl: task + notifications
    Ctrl-->>API: 201 Created
    API-->>FE: success
    FE-->>U: Task assigned
    
    
    Note over U,Ext: Create Task Reminder

    %% Scenario 2: Create Task Reminder
    note right of U: Create Task Reminder
    
    U->>FE: Set reminder for task
    FE->>API: POST /task-reminders {taskId, reminderTime}
    API->>Ctrl: createReminder()
    Ctrl->>Svc: validateReminderData()
    Svc->>DB: find({taskId, userId})
    DB-->>Svc: task exists
    Svc->>DB: insertOne(reminder)
    DB-->>Svc: reminder created
    Svc->>Queue: add('schedule-reminder', delay)
    Queue-->>Queue: Scheduled job
    Svc-->>Ctrl: reminder object
    Ctrl-->>API: 201 Created
    API-->>FE: reminder set
    FE-->>U: Reminder created
    
    Note over U,Ext: Reminder Time Arrives
    %% Scenario 3: Reminder Triggered
    
    note right of Queue: Reminder Time Arrives
    Queue->>Queue: Process scheduled job
    Queue->>Svc: processReminder()
    Svc->>DB: findReminder(jobId)
    DB-->>Svc: reminder object
    Svc->>DB: findTask(taskId)
    DB-->>Svc: task details
    Svc->>DB: insertOne(notification)
    DB-->>Svc: notification created
    alt Channel: Push
        Svc->>Queue: add('send-push')
        Queue->>Ext: FCM/APNs
        Ext-->>Queue: delivered
    else Channel: Email
        Svc->>Queue: add('send-email')
        Queue->>Ext: SendGrid
        Ext-->>Queue: delivered
    else Channel: SMS
        Svc->>Queue: add('send-sms')
        Queue->>Ext: Twilio
        Ext-->>Queue: delivered
    end
    Svc->>DB: updateOne(reminder, {status: sent})
    Svc-->>Queue: complete
    
    Note over U,Ext: View Notifications
    %% Scenario 4: Get User Notifications
    
    note right of U: View Notifications
    U->>FE: Open notifications
    FE->>API: GET /notifications/my?page=1&limit=10
    API->>Ctrl: getMyNotifications()
    Ctrl->>Cache: get(userId:notifications)
    alt Cache Hit
        Cache-->>Ctrl: cached notifications
        Ctrl-->>API: cached data
    else Cache Miss
        Ctrl->>Svc: getNotifications(userId, options)
        Svc->>DB: find({receiverId}).sort(-createdAt)
        DB-->>Svc: notifications[]
        Svc->>Cache: setex(key, 60, notifications)
        Svc-->>Ctrl: notifications
    end
    Ctrl-->>API: 200 OK
    API-->>FE: notifications
    FE-->>U: Display notifications
    
    Note over U,Ext: Mark as Read
    %% Scenario 5: Mark Notification as Read
    
    note right of U: Mark as Read
    U->>FE: Click notification
    FE->>API: POST /notifications/:id/read
    API->>Ctrl: markAsRead(id)
    Ctrl->>Svc: markAsRead(userId, id)
    Svc->>DB: updateOne({_id, receiverId}, {status: read, readAt: now})
    DB-->>Svc: updated
    Svc->>Cache: del(userId:notifications)
    Svc->>Cache: del(userId:unreadCount)
    Svc-->>Ctrl: 200 OK
    Ctrl-->>API: success
    API-->>FE: marked read
    FE-->>U: Notification opened
    
    Note over U,Ext: Check Unread Badge
    %% Scenario 6: Get Unread Count
    
    note right of U: Check Unread Badge
    U->>FE: Open app
    FE->>API: GET /notifications/unread-count
    API->>Ctrl: getUnreadCount()
    Ctrl->>Cache: get(userId:unreadCount)
    alt Cache Hit
        Cache-->>Ctrl: count
        Ctrl-->>API: cached count
    else Cache Miss
        Ctrl->>Svc: countUnread(userId)
        Svc->>DB: count({receiverId, status: unread})
        DB-->>Svc: count
        Svc->>Cache: setex(key, 30, count)
        Svc-->>Ctrl: count
    end
    Ctrl-->>API: 200 OK
    API-->>FE: count
    FE-->>U: Show badge
    
    Note over U,Ext: Cancel Reminder
    %% Scenario 7: Cancel Reminder
    
    note right of U: Cancel Reminder
    U->>FE: Click cancel reminder
    FE->>API: DELETE /task-reminders/:id
    API->>Ctrl: cancelReminder(id)
    Ctrl->>Svc: cancelReminder(userId, id)
    Svc->>DB: find({_id, userId})
    DB-->>Svc: reminder object
    alt Is Owner
        Svc->>Queue: removeJob(jobId)
        Queue-->>Svc: job removed
        Svc->>DB: updateOne({status: cancelled})
        DB-->>Svc: updated
        Svc-->>Ctrl: 200 OK
        Ctrl-->>API: success
        API-->>FE: cancelled
        FE-->>U: Reminder cancelled
    else Not Owner
        Svc-->>Ctrl: 403 Forbidden
        Ctrl-->>API: 403
        API-->>FE: error
        FE-->>U: Permission denied
    end
    
    
    %% Note over U,Ext: All notifications support multi-channel delivery

    
    %% Scenario 8: Recurring Reminder
    
    note right of Queue: Recurring Reminder
    Queue->>Queue: Process recurring job
    Queue->>Svc: processRecurringReminder()
    Svc->>DB: findReminder(jobId)
    DB-->>Svc: reminder object
    alt Has More Occurrences
        Svc->>Svc: sendNotification()
        Svc->>DB: increment(sentCount)
        Svc->>DB: calculateNextOccurrence()
        Svc->>Queue: add('schedule-reminder', nextTime)
        Svc-->>Queue: rescheduled
    else Max Occurrences Reached
        Svc->>DB: updateOne({status: completed})
        Svc-->>Queue: complete
    end
    
    
    Note over U,Ext: All notifications support multi-channel delivery
